other_tests.findings: Marked dilatation of a fluid-filled appendix, measuring up to 11 mm in diameter; a 4-mm appendicolith seen within the mid appendix; periappendiceal fat stranding without fluid collection or evidence of perforation.

Minimal left basilar atelectasis, tiny hypodensity within hepatic segment VII likely a simple cyst; unremarkable liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, and left kidney; small hypodensity in right upper pole renal area uncharacterized; stomach, small bowel, and colon grossly unremarkable; small quantity of free fluid in pelvis.
